commit.message:
Fix for cross-domain d3.dsv in IE9.

In some cases IE9 processes the opening of an XDomainRequest synchronously, so
by the time we were setting the response function to parse the DSV file, it was
too late. So instead we use the internal d3_xhr method to set the response
function before the request is sent. This is a continuation of fix #1260.
include d3 shim config for jspm
Use a proper lognormal CDF approximation
Use seed random to seed Math.random
Remove author tag (consistency with other d3 source)
Add author tag (so you know who to blame when hull breaks)
Rename some test cases (point sets aren’t polygons)

Merge branch 'master' into better-hull2

Conflicts:
	d3.min.js
Remove console.logs and add more comments
Implement a bunch of RNG tests including K-S test
Merge branch 'filter-fix' of git://github.com/natevw/d3 into filter-group-index

Avoid flipping longitude near ±π.

When computing the midpoint between two points both at longitude -π, there was a
chance that atan2 would return +π rather than -π. Now, we check whether the
points to interpolate lie (approximately) on a meridian; if they do, we can
approximate by using linear interpolation of longitude rather than atan2. This
fixes #1635 which was caused by new trig implementations in Chrome Canary.
Simpler update between ordinal & quantitative scales.

Fix transform for ordinal→quantitative scales.

Previously, invalid transform attributes were being set for an
ordinal→quantitative scale transition, because entering ticks were
undefined in the old (ordinal) scale, and exiting ticks were undefined
in the new (quantitative) scale.

Fixes #1620.

Implement monotone chain convex hull (faster and cleaner)
pass subgroup/parent/"j" index to filter function for consistency with most everything else
